2%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663cfffcb4abc992e8c77644%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22945%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoving%20to%20Taiwan%20helped%20the%20couple%20pay%20off%20debt%2C%20but%20being%20far%20from%20Canada%20came%20with%20some%20challenges.%20%3Cp%3EBecky%20Martin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20is%20a%20child%20and%20youth%20worker%2C%20while%20Schmidt%20is%20a%20graphic%20designer.%20When%20they%20lived%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20they%20both%20worked%20as%20English%20teachers.%20In%202004%2C%20after%20two%20years%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20during%20which%20they%20moved%20three%20times%2C%20the%20couple%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20Canada%2C%20in%20part%20so%20they%20could%20return%20to%20their%20careers%20and%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20bounced%20around%20to%20several%20different%20residences%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%20but%20set%20out%20to%20live%20a%20%26quot%3Btraditional%20married%20life%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20they%20excelled%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20found%20a%20home%2C%20had%20kids%2C%20and%20lived%20%26quot%3Bhappily%20ever%20after%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20found%20this%20dream%20difficult%20to%20accomplish%2C%20in%20part%20because%20their%20finances%20began%20to%20strain%20again%2C%20and%20debt%20started%20piling%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20in%202009%2C%20the%20couple%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20to%20Taiwan.%20Martin%20said%20they%20paid%20off%20about%20%2433%2C000%20in%20debt%20(%2445%2C000%20in%20Canadian%20dollars)%20in%20a%20year-and-a-half%20and%20lived%20in%20an%20apartment%20with%20a%20beautiful%20view%20for%20less%20than%20%241%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20knew%20the%20job%2C%20the%20culture%2C%20the%20weather%2C%20expectations%2C%20and%20how%20much%20money%20we%20could%20make%20and%20save%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20they%20stayed%20in%20Taiwan%20for%20over%20seven%20years%2C%20moving%20twice%20during%20this%20span.%20But%20they%20eventually%20found%20themselves%20missing%20family%20and%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20over%2012%2C000%20kilometers%20away%20from%20people%20meant%20that%20you%20couldn't%20share%20your%20life%20with%20those%20important%20to%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20aging%20parents%20and%20some%20deaths%20in%20the%20family%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20move%20back%20to%20Canada%20for%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bhidden%20costs%20of%20moving%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20included%20having%20to%20say%20goodbye%20to%20meaningful%20relationships%2C%20had%20become%20apparent%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20we%20left%2C%20our%20foundation%20would%20crumble%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20to%20start%20making%20a%20solid%20foundation%20if%20we%20wanted%20a%20solid%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222806b727-8542-4215-ab9c-c8ededebe627%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20best%20places%20to%20live%20in%20Asia%20from%20a%20financial%20perspective%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20said%20it%20took%20them%20some%20time%20to%20transition%20back%20to%20Canada%20and%20figure%20out%20where%20they%20wanted%20to%20settle%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20initially%20moved%20back%20to%20Stratford%2C%20Ontario%20before%20moving%20to%20Kitchener%2C%20where%20they've%20resided%20for%20about%20the%20last%20five%20years.%20Martin%20said%20Kitchener%20is%20close%20enough%20to%20Toronto%20to%20enjoy%20the%20city%20but%20far%20enough%20away%20to%20avoid%20the%20high%20costs%20and%20congestion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20financial%20perspective%2C%20Martin%20said%20she%20doesn't%20think%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20place%26quot%3B%20to%20live%20in%20Canada%20%E2%80%94%20you%20just%20have%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20make%20it%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCanada%20is%20expensive%20and%20the%20only%20cheaper%20places%20are%20far%20north%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20further%20north%20you%20go%2C%20the%20cheaper%20it%20gets%2C%20but%20it's%20far%20away%20from%20most%20people%2C%20job%20opportunities%2C%20and%20nicer%20weather.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20Martin's%20personal%20research%20and%20experience%2C%20she%20said%20Taiwan%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20places%20in%20Asia%20that%20checks%20two%20boxes%3A%20low%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20relatively%20high%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJapan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Singapore%2C%20and%20big%20cities%20in%20China%20are%20all%20very%20expensive%20places%20to%20live%20%E2%80%94%20you%20make%20more%20but%20pay%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20decide%20on%20places%20like%20the%20Philippines%2C%20Thailand%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20and%20India%2C%20are%20all%20exciting%20and%20beautiful%20places%2C%20but%20pay%20little.%20The%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20low%2C%20but%20so%20is%20your%20salary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20said%20the%20language%20barrier%20was%20one%20of%20the%20main%20downsides%20of%20living%20in%20Taiwan.%20She%20said%20Mandarin%2C%20a%20common%20language%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20is%20a%20very%20difficult%20language%20to%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20stress%20and%20financial%20challenges%20that%20came%20with%20moving%20so%20often%2C%20Martin%20said%20she%20has%20%26quot%3Bno%20regrets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20learned%20so%20much%20about%20myself%20by%20starting%20over%20again%20and%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20relationship%20with%20Craig%20has%20only%20gotten%20stronger%20and%20we%20have%20a%20million%20stories%20and%20experiences%20to%20talk%20about%20and%20revisit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20strengthened%20our%20marriage%20and%20gave%20us%20opportunities%20to%20reinvent%20ourselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEach%20time%20we%20moved%2C%20it%20was%20for%20a%20good%20reason.%2