Cspan%3Ealmost%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Enail%20the%20spelling%20before%20school.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-mom-of-3-kids-survives-first-weeks-of-school-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20day%20at%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20still%20been%20confusing.%20I'd%20come%20out%20asking%20my%20mom%20why%20the%20teachers%20couldn't%20say%20my%20name.%20It%20was%20a%20curveball%20among%20the%20Sophies%20and%20Matthews%2C%20and%20nobody%20else%20in%20my%20first%20primary%20school%20class%20had%20a%20non-English%20name.%20It%20felt%20isolating%20when%20teachers%20knew%20everyone%20else's%20names%20straight%20away.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1cb17fc-0131-4c7a-b072-1586e72e2b18%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20amplified%20my%20social%20anxiety%20in%20my%20school%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20high%20school%20there%20were%20others%20with%20unusual%20names%2C%20so%20I%20wasn't%20the%20only%20one%20having%20to%20explain%20pronunciations%20at%20registration.%20However%2C%20at%20around%2012%20years%20old%2C%20my%20social%20anxiety%20tripled.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-suffers-self-doubt-over-public-speaking-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20speaking%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20basically%20speaking%20to%20anyone%20more%20than%20on%20a%20one-to-one%20basis%2C%20could%20bring%20uncontrollable%20shaking%2C%20dizzy%20spells%2C%20and%20stuttering%20words%20that%20refused%20to%20flow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20dreaded%20speaking%20up%20and%20explaining%20my%20name%20to%20yet%20another%20supply%20teacher%20in%20front%20of%20a%20class%20of%20over%2030%20people.%20The%20start%20of%20the%20new%20school%20year%20was%20a%20nightmare%2C%20too%2C%20explaining%20my%20name%20to%20each%20teacher%20repeatedly%20until%20they%20cracked%20it%20or%20I%20finally%20accepted%20a%20slightly%20remixed%20version.%20Heaven%20forbid%20I%20ever%20got%20called%20on%20in%20assemblies%20when%20nearly%20300%20pupils%20crammed%20into%20a%20single%20hall.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20that%20constant%20worry%20amplified%20my%20already%20lurking%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fsocial-anxiety-disorder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esocial%20anxiety%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20also%20added%20to%20the%20usual%20teenage%20angst%20of%20struggling%20to%20find%20myself.%20You'd%20think%20having%20to%20explain%20pronunciation%20constantly%20would%20have%20helped%20me%20forge%20a%20more%20solid%20identity%2C%20but%20it%20actually%20did%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20worsened%20my%20people-pleasing%20tendencies%20when%20I'd%20just%20accept%20wrong%20pronunciations%3B%20I%20was%20called%20%26quot%3BEeblis%26quot%3B%20for%20about%20two%20years%20by%20one%20science%20teacher.%20Instead%20of%20embracing%20my%20name%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20shrinking%20it%20to%20avoid%20the%20potential%20anxiety.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20days%2C%20I%20wished%20the%20floor%20would%20swallow%20me%20up%2C%20most%20notably%20when%20my%20geography%20teacher%20somehow%20got%20%26quot%3BElvis%26quot%3B%20from%20my%20name%20on%20the%20register%2C%20and%20everyone%20burst%20out%20laughing.%20It%20took%20me%20a%20long%20time%20to%20realize%20that%20my%20name%20was%20an%20identity%2C%20not%20a%20butt%20of%20a%20joke.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a7c81cf4-a9af-42a2-8e64-d406126458e3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20I%20love%20my%20name%20and%20its%20nod%20to%20my%20heritage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGradually%2C%20though%2C%20something%20shifted.%20I%20learned%20my%20name's%20meaning%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BGod%20is%20my%20oath%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20Irish%20Gaelic%20adaptation%20of%20the%20name%20Elizabeth.%20I%20realized%20how%20endangered%20the%20Irish%20language%20was%20and%20how%20proud%20I%20was%20to%20carry%20that%20symbol%20of%20my%20heritage.%20I%20began%20to%20embrace%20the%20story%20it%20held%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20twins%20to%20my%20family%20history%20and%2C%20eventually%2C%20how%20it%20pushed%20me%20out%20of%20my%20comfort%20zone%20in%20those%20formative%20school%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20all%2C%20my%20name%20never%20let%20me%20sit%20quietly%20in%20the%20back%20of%20a%20classroom%2C%20even%20when%20that's%20all%20I%20wanted%20to%20do.%20And%20for%20that%2C%20I'm%20very%20grateful.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funusual-name-social-anxiety-kid-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715419921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663cd42b9686a6f37bfd8c7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funusual-name-social-anxiety-kid-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20parents%20named%20me%20Eibhlis%2C%20which%20I%20could%20spell%20by%20the%20time%20I%20was%204.%20Still%2C%20I%20had%20social%20anxiety%20while%20in%20school%20because%20of%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eibhlis%20Gale-Coleman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funusual-name-social-anxiety-kid-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Priyanka%20Chopra%20hails%20'Heeramandi'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715419905000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110033001%2Cimgsize-44306.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fen