he%20grief%20that%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fson-died-at-home-family-still-lives-there-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoms%20who%20lose%20their%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%20feel.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20move%20on%20or%20erase%20memories%20of%20Alex.%20As%20I%20struggled%20with%20Alex's%20death%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20move%20forward%2C%20somehow%20integrating%20his%20death%20into%20my%20significantly%20altered%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELife%20has%20gone%20on%20for%20me%2C%20for%20us.%20Both%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnon-traditional-strategies-retire-millionaires-2023-03%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehusband%20and%20I%20retired%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20our%20jobs%20in%20the%20Rutgers%20University%20Department%20of%20Sociology.%20We%20loved%20teaching%20and%20research%2C%20but%20we%20were%20ready%20for%20change.%20We%20moved%20to%20Washington%2C%20DC.%2C%20and%20I%2C%20for%20one%2C%20am%20ready%20for%20activism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20hasn't%20been%20easy%20to%20move%20forward%20from%20the%20dark%20days.%20Often%20it%20has%20been%20horrifyingly%20hard.%20But%20when%20people%20ask%2C%20I%20always%20say%20I%20just%20put%20one%20foot%20in%20front%20of%20the%20other.%20There%20really%20isn't%20any%20other%20way%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4789d54-fa93-4df2-9a8e-70fc3c92081a%5C%22%3EWe%20were%20numb%20at%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-support-grieving-parents-after-the-loss-of-child-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshock%20of%20your%20child's%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20disorienting.%20Life%20changes%20in%20an%20instant.%20We%20were%20numb%2C%20in%20shock%2C%20I%20suppose.%20The%20tears%20came%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20tell%20our%20relatives%2C%20close%20friends%2C%20and%20colleagues%20to%20let%20them%20know%20the%20horror%20that%20had%20befallen%20our%20family.%20Our%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20responders%26quot%3B%20arrived%20almost%20immediately%20to%20take%20care%20of%20us.%20When%20day%20turned%20to%20evening%2C%20I%20took%20enough%20Ambien%20to%20ensure%20I%20could%20sleep%20through%20the%20night%2C%20more%20than%20I%20had%20ever%20taken%20in%20the%20past.%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20alert%20the%20next%20day.%20There%20was%20no%20time%20for%20insomnia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20week%20occupied%20us%20with%20the%20chores%20and%20rituals%20that%20follow%20a%20death%20in%20the%20family.%20We%20met%20with%20the%20funeral%20director%2C%20who%20had%20been%20Alex's%20Little%20League%20coach.%20We%20decided%20on%20a%20non-church%20service%20and%20chose%20to%20cremate%20our%20beautiful%20boy.%20We%20also%20decided%20not%20to%20view%20Alex's%20body%2C%20a%20choice%20I%20sometimes%20regret.%20But%20the%20thought%20of%20seeing%20Alex%20dead%20was%20unbearable.%20This%20meant%20that%20I%20was%20never%20fully%20convinced%20that%20Alex%20died.%20But%20our%20friend%2C%20the%20funeral%20director%2C%20confirmed%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20wrote%20Alex's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funusual-unique-obituaries-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobituary%20and%20eulogy%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20Celebration%20of%20Life.%20I%20needed%20to%20honor%20my%20child's%20memory%2C%20to%20try%20to%20give%20meaning%20to%20a%20life%20cut%20short%2C%20to%20acknowledge%20all%20of%20who%20he%20was.%20I%20also%20felt%20strongly%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20take%20a%20public%20stand%20against%20stigma%2C%20to%20step%20out%20of%20the%20shadows.%20I%20wanted%20to%20shine%20a%20light%20on%20addiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20week%20was%20the%20longest%20week%20of%20my%20life%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20the%20hardest.%20That%20came%20after.%20We%20had%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20pieces%20and%20learn%20to%20live%20again.%20We%20escaped%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20fleeing%20to%20Montauk%2C%20one%20of%20our%20special%20places.%20I%20knew%20we%20needed%20to%20get%20away%20from%20New%20Jersey%20for%20Christmas.%20For%20the%20next%20four%20years%2C%20we%20spent%20Christmas%20away%20from%20home%2C%20mostly%20in%20the%20Caribbean.%20It%20worked.%20By%202019%2C%20we%20were%20ready%20to%20be%20home%20for%20the%20holidays.%20We%20even%20found%20some%20joy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222011fbf5-4b6a-40e4-b70a-ff44884041c2%5C%22%3EI%20wanted%20to%20know%20more%20about%20addiction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20my%20quest%20to%20understand%20why%20addiction%20happened%20to%20my%20family%20by%20intellectualizing%20my%20experiences%20and%20asking%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhow%26quot%3B%20questions%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20read%20historical%20and%20sociological%20studies%3B%20I%20studied%20policy%20research%20on%20addiction%20and%20the%20strategies%20to%20combat%20it.%20I%20learned%20about%20harm%20reduction%2C%20which%20I%20now%20think%20is%20the%20most%20promising%20strategy%20for%20combatting%20the%20scourge%20of%20addiction.%20I%20broadened%20my%20readings%20from%20scholarship%20and%20journalism%20to%20memoirs.%20These%20personal%20narratives%20describe%20mental%20health%2C%20substance%20use%2C%20and%20pain%20and%20suffering%20in%20raw%20and%20unfiltered%20ways%2C%20showing%20how%20they%20destroy%20the%20lives%20of%20children%2C%20families%2C%20neighbors%2C%20and%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20intellectualizing%20my%20experiences%20was%20helpful%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20needed%20more%20than%20reading%20to%20find%20understanding.%20I%20searched%20for%20social%20communities%2C%20first%20online%20and%20then%20in%20person%20through%2012-step%20and%20grief%20groups.%20The%20people%20I%20met%20in%20my%20Naranon%20and%20grief%20groups%20provided%20invaluable%20fellowship%2C%20and%20several%20remain%20my%20grief%20buddies.%20But%20I%20was%20still%20searching.%20I%20tried%20other%20forms%20of%20self-care%2C%20including%20yoga%2C%20walking%2C%20and%20meditation.%20A%20friend%20even%20brought%20me%20to%20a%20psychic.%20When%20I%20mentioned%20it%20to%20my%20fellow%20travelers%20in%20grief%2C%20three%20of%20the%20moms%2C%20but%20none%20of%20the%20dads%2C%20had%20done%20the%20same%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20it%20was%20writing%20and%20my%20turn%20toward%20activism%20that%20really%20helped%20to%20pull%20me%20out%20of%20the%20shadows.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20I%20shift%20to%20this%20new%20stage%20of%20my%20life%2C%20my%20expanded%20social%20communities%20and%20my%20family%20have%20given%20me%20the%20support%2C%20encouragement%2C%20and%20purpose%20I%20need.%20I%20have%20a%20wound%20that%20will%20never%20completely%20heal%2C%20but%20telling%20my%20story%20has%20made%20things%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPatricia%20A.%20Roos%20wrote%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpatroos.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESurviving%20Alex%3A%20A%20Mother's%20Story%20of%20Love%2C%20Loss%2C%20and%20Addiction%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20published%20May%2017%2C%202024%20by%20Rutgers%20University%20Press.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-child-died-mothers-day-wound-will-never-heal-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715418121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663ce08cb4abc992e8c74521%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-child-died-mothers-day-wound-will-never-heal-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20found%20out%20my%20son%20had%20died%20of%20an%20overdose%20days%20after%20Mother's%20Day.%20I%20sometimes%20wonder%20how%20I've%20survived%20all%20these%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Patricia%20Roos)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-child-died-mothers-day-wound-will-never-heal-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20US%20Army's%20new%20plan%20to%20counter%20Russia%20and%20China%20has%20a%20glaring%20problem%2C%20experts%20say%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Soldiers%20in%20training%20on%20a%2012-mile%20ruck%20march%20at%20Fort%20Moore%2C%20Georgia%20in%20January.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e4c5ef27898f532d64da1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESoldiers%20in%20training%20on%20a%2012-mile%20ruck%20march%20at%20Fort%20Moore%2C%20Georgia%20in%20January.%3Cp%3ECapt.%20Stephanie%20Snyder%2FUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Army's%20new%20structure%20responds%20to%20drones%20and%20guided%20missiles%20and%20artillery.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20Army%20plans%20to%20stand%20up%20new%20units%20at%20a%20time%20its%20recruiting%20is%20struggling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Army%20is%20also%20basing%20its%20plans%20on%20untried%20weapons%2C%20the%20Congressional%20Research%20Service%20warned.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20Army%20is%20reorganizing%20to%20fight%20against%20major%20powers%20like%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20but%20it%20lacks%20the%20troops%20and%20new%20recruits%20to%20carry%20it%20out%2C%20congressional%20analysts%20contend.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202024%20Army%20Force%20Structure%20Transformation%20would%20be%20the%20Army's%20fifth%20major%20reorganization%20since%202003.%20Judging%20by%20details%20laid%20out%20in%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapi.army.mil%2Fe2%2Fc%2Fdownloads%2F2024%2F02%2F27%2F091989c9%2Farmy-white-paper-army-force-structure-transformation.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArmy%20white%20paper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20emphasis%20will%20be%20on%20responding%20to%20technological%20changes%20in%20warfare%2C%20such%20as%20the%20threat%20of%20drones%20and%20long-range%20guided%20munitions%2C%20while%20trying%20to%20economize%20on%20scarce%20manpower.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20that%20may%20be%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20one%20thing%20to%20establish%20the%20authorizations%20for%20new%20and%20existing%20units%20discussed%20in%20the%20Army's%20white%20paper%2C%20yet%20another%20to%20fill%20those%20authorizations%20with%20qualified%20soldiers%2C%26quot%3B%20warns%20a%20new%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FR%2FR47985%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20Congressional%20Research%20Service%2C%20which%20analyzes%20issues%20for%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20striking%20aspect%20of%20the%20Army's%20plan%20is%20the%20large%20number%20of%20new%20units%2C%20for%20counter-drone%20protection%20as%20well%20as%20air%20and%20missile%20defense.%20These%20units%2C%20assigned%20to%20corps-%20and%20division-level%20formations%2C%20would%20include%20four%20more%20%26quot%3Bindirect%20fire%20protection%20capability%26quot%3B%20battalions%20intended%20to%20shoot%20down%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20rockets%2C%20and%20artillery%20and%20mortar%20shells.%20In%20addition%2C%20there%20would%20be%20nine%20counter-small%20UAS%20batteries%20tasked%20with%20destroying%20small%20drones%2C%20and%20four%20more%20Maneuver%20Short%20Range%20Air%20Defense%20(M-SHORAD)%20battalions%20to%20stop%20manned%20aircraft%2C%20helicopters%20and%20drones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20would%20help%20flesh%20out%20the%20Army's%20five%20Multi-Domain%20Task%20Forces%2C%20theater-level%20units%20with%20exotic%20capabilities%20such%20as%20hypersonic%20missiles%2C%20cyberwarfare%2C%20jamming%2C%20and%20integrating%20intelligence%20data.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20trying%20to%20address%20a%20recruiting%20crisis%20that%20has%20left%20some%20units%20undermanned.%20The%20transformation%20plan%20would%20reduce%20authorized%20strength%20%E2%80%94%20the%20maximum%20number%20of%20soldiers%20allowed%20%E2%80%94%20from%20494%2C000%20to%20470%2C000.%20The%20Army%20currently%20has%20about%20450%2C000%20active-duty%20troops.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20US%20Army%20had%20770%2C000%20soldiers%20in%20the%20latter%20stages%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20when%20it%20was%20structured%20to%20counter%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20will%20shrink%20excess%2C%20largely%20unmanned%20'hollow'%20force%20structure%20and%20build%20new%20formations%20equipped%20with%20new%20capabilities%20needed%20for%20large%20scale%20combat%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Army%20white%20paper%20explained.%20This%20would%20include%203%2C000%20fewer%20authorized%20special%20operations%20forces%20personnel.%20Some%20functions%20will%20also%20be%20consolidated%2C%20such%20as%20reassigning%20engineers%20from%20brigade%20combat%20teams%20to%20divisions%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20fewer%20engineer%20slots.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20even%20with%20consolidation%20and%20a%20boost%20to%20recruitment%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armytimes.com%2Fnews%2Fyour-army%2F2024%2F01%2F02%2Farmy-to-open-applications-for-new-recruiting-warrant-officer-field%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%20warrant%20officers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20who%20specialize%20in%20recruiting%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Army%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20find%20enough%20personnel%20to%20fill%20out%20its%20existing%20units%20and%20create%20new%20air%20defense%20formations.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20Army%20came%20up%2010%2C000%20short%20in%20its%20quest%20for%2065%2C000%20new%20recruits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20past%20recruiting%20shortfalls%20and%20preliminary%20FY2024%20recruiting%20data%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20predict%20if%20the%20Army%20will%20be%20able%20rectify%20its%20recruiting%20challenges%20in%20the%20near%20and%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20CRS%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Army%20may%20also%20be%20focusing%20too%20much%20on%20cutting-edge%20%26quot%3Bsoft%26quot%3B%20technologies%20rather%20than%20old-fashioned%20kinetic%20weapons%20that%20have%20proven%20quite%20relevant%20and%20lethal%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20white%20paper%20appears%20to%20address%20technology-based%2C%20non-kinetic%20space%20and%20cyber%20effects%2C%20long-range%20precision%20fires%2C%20and%20force%20protection%20more%20than%20it%20does%20conventional%20close-combat%20force%20capabilities%2C%20Army%20Special%20Operations%20Forces%20capabilities%2C%20and%20Security%20Force%20Assistance%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20CRS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%205-kilowatt%20laser%20sits%20on%20a%20Stryker%20armored%20vehicle%20in%202017.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e3b2eb4abc992e8c808cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221343%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%205-kilowatt%20laser%20sits%20on%20a%20Stryker%20armored%20vehicle%20in%202017.%3Cp%3EMonica%20K.%20Guthrie%2FUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Army%20is%20also%20basing%20its%20plans%20on%20untried%20weapons%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Long-Range%20Hypersonic%20Missile%20and%20air%20defense%20lasers.%20%26quot%3BSome%20units%2C%20such%20as%20LRHW%20batteries%20and%20Directed%20Energy%20(DE)%20SHORAD%20units%2C%20do%20not%20have%20mature%20weapons%20and%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20CRS%20warned.%20Nor%20does%20the%20Army%20%E2%80%94%20or%20Congress%20%E2%80%94%20have%20a%20good%20idea%20of%20how%20much%20the%20reorganization%20would%20cost.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInevitably%2C%20there%20will%20also%20be%20disruptions%20caused%20by%20yet%20another%20Army%20metamorphosis.%20In%202003%2C%20the%20Army%20switched%20from%20a%20Cold%20War%20force%20structure%20of%20heavy%20mechanized%20divisions%2C%20to%20smaller%2C%20lighter%20brigades%20more%20suitable%20for%20counterinsurgency.%20Now%2C%20the%20Army%20has%20gone%20full%20circle%20as%20it%20reconfigures%20for%20Cold%20War-style%20mechanized%20conflict%20against%20big%20opponents%20like%20Russia%20and%20China.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20must%20also%20incorporate%20new%20technologies%20such%20as%20drones%20and%20long-range%20artillery%2C%20which%20have%20demonstrated%20their%20power%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reorganization%20does%20address%20some%20of%20the%20Army's%20problems%2C%20Mark%20Cancian%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20new%20units%C2%A0are%20appropriate%20for%20a%C2%A0great%20power%20conflict.%C2%A0China%20and%20Russia%20have%20much%20stronger%20air%20and%20missile%20forces%20than%20the%20regional%C2%A0opponents%20the%20army%20has%20faced%20for%20the%20last%20generation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECreating%20units%20armed%20with%20hypersonic%20missiles%20also%20makes%20sense%2C%20especially%20since%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%20withdrew%20in%202019%20from%20the%20Intermediate-Range%20Nuclear%20Forces%20treaty%2C%20signed%20in%201987%20to%20curb%20cruise%20missiles%20and%20other%20medium-range%20nuclear%20weapons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20long-range%20fires%20are%20an%20opportunity%20that%20has%20opened%20up%20with%20the%20end%20of%20the%20INF%2C%26quot%3B%20Cancian%20said.%20Nonetheless%2C%20the%20reorganization%20doesn't%20address%20the%20real%20issue.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Army's%20major%20problem%20is%20that%20it%20is%20too%20small%20overall%20to%20meet%20all%20of%20its%20likely%20peacetime%20and%20wartime%20commitments%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cancian.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20an%20MA%20in%20political%20science%20from%20Rutgers%20Univ.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ETwitter%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmipeck%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-armys-new-plan-russia-china-glaring-problem-crs-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715418001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e4c9af27898f532d64e1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-armys-new-plan-russia-china-glaring-problem-crs-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20Army%20is%20reorganizing%20to%20respond%20to%20rising%20threats%2C%20but%20standing%20up%20new%20units%20is%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Michael%20Peck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-armys-new-plan-russia-china-glaring-problem-crs-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20bodybuilder%20ditched%20his%20low-carb%20diet%20and%20started%20eating%20potatoes%206%20times%20a%20day.%20He%20got%20in%20the%20best%20shape%20of%20his%20life.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D