l%20institutions%2C%20employing%20a%20unique%20educational%20model%2C%EF%BF%BD%20Juin%20explains.%20%EF%BF%BDGiven%20the%20diverse%20backgrounds%20of%20our%20students%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20commence%20their%20education%20later%20in%20life%2C%20we%EF%BF%BDve%20adopted%20a%20levelled%20system%20of%20instruction.%20In%20our%20approach%2C%20a%20student%EF%BF%BDs%20level%20in%20a%20particular%20subject%20is%20determined%20by%20their%20proficiency%20rather%20than%20their%20age%2C%20ensuring%20no%20one%20feels%20misplaced%20or%20ashamed%20for%20joining%20later.%EF%BF%BD%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%EF%BF%BDWe%20also%20prioritise%20sports%20and%20project-based%20activities%2C%20offering%20opportunities%20for%20learning%20beyond%20the%20conventional%20curriculum%2C%20such%20as%20painting%2C%20judo%2C%20and%20karate%2C%EF%BF%BD%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJuin%20goes%20on%20to%20explain%20the%20entire%20process%20of%20how%20a%20student%20is%20assigned%20a%20particular%20lever%20and%20how%20they%20navigate%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%EF%BF%BDWhen%20a%20child%20joins%20Pathshala%2C%20we%20assess%20their%20current%20knowledge%20and%20comprehension%20abilities%20in%20languages%20and%20mathematics.%20Based%20on%20this%20evaluation%2C%20we%20place%20them%20in%20appropriate%20levels%20corresponding%20to%20their%20proficiency.%20Consequently%2C%20each%20child%20studies%20at%20different%20levels%20for%20various%20subjects.%20Upon%20completion%20of%20Level%205%2C%20a%20student%20becomes%20equivalent%20to%20be%20eligible%20to%20sit%20for%20Class%208%2C%EF%BF%BD%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20Class%208%20to%2012%2C%20the%20school%20adheres%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Open%20Schooling%20(NIOS)%20syllabus%2C%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStudents%20take%20psychometric%20tests%20to%20discover%20their%20career%20inclinations%2C%20guiding%20their%20subject%20choices%20when%20they%20enter%20Class%208.%20This%20personalised%20method%20ensures%20their%20inte